sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1937004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: (Chassis B. subtilis, carrier plasmid pBS0K) Length: 6843 bp Background: pNagA is the promoter of the NagA gene, which expresses a N-acetylglucosamine-6-phosphate deacetylasein in Bacillus subtilis. In bacillus subtilis, this promoter has been reported to induce expression in presence of N-acetylglucosamine 6-phosphate. This NAG molecule is the major component of chitin, a characteristic molecule of fungi. This BioBrick is a part developed by the Toulouse 2016 iGEM team (http://2016.igem.org/Team:Toulouse_France)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Oumnia KARIM
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
The part include the pNagA promoter and its RBS (position 3,595,156 to 3,595,356 of the Bacillus genome). The promoter controls the expression of the RFP fluorescent reporter gene. A NheI restriction site has been placed before the RFP ORF to facilitate promoter swapping.This part is a subcloning of BBa_K1937003 pNagA part in pSBBS0K_mini plasmid (BBa_K1937001).
In bacillus subtilis, this promoter has been reported to induce expression in presence of N-acetylglucosamine 6-phosphate.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1937001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pSBBsOK-mini, a small replicative plasmid for Bacillus subtilis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Part: BBa_K1937001 (pSBBsOK-mini) (Chassis E. coli, carrier plasmid pSB1C3, part destined for use in Bacillus subtilis) Length: 5857 bp
This part is an expression vector for Bacillus subtilis. It is replicative both in E.coli and B.subtilis. It has an ampicillin resistance for cloning in E.coli and kanamycin resistance for selection in B. subtilis. This BioBrick is a part developed by the Toulouse 2016 iGEM team (http://2016.igem.org/Team:Toulouse_France)
We successfully transformed E. coli and selected clones on ampicillin. Likewise, we successfully transformed B. subtilis and selected clones on kanamycine. The plasmid sequence has been entirely verified by sequencing. The capacity to sub-clone in this new backbone has been demonstrated (part BBa_K1937004, BBa_K1937006, BBa_K1937008 and BBa_K1937010).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Brice Enjalbert
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was created by amplifying a 5827pb fragment from the pSBBsOK -P plasmid (BBa_K1351040) using primers pSBBsOK Forward (5??? ctgctggctagcTACTAGTAGCGGCCGCTGCAGGCGCAACGCAATTAATGTGAGTTAGG) and pSBBsOK Reverse (5??? gacgacgctagcCTCTAGAAGCGGCCGCGAATTcAAATCAGCAAGGGACAGGTAG). The PCR product was digested by NheI and ligated on himself. The resulting plasmid is a lighter shuttle plasmid (E. coli and B. subtilis) with all the properties of the iGEM pSBA13 plasmid (prefix, suffix, verification sequences???).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The pSBBsOK-mini is a reduction of the pSBBsOK -P plasmid (BBa_K1351040). Its size is only 5827 pb compared to the entire pSBBsOK -P which is 9358 pb long.
